history.content:
My phase1 starts at Oct22 (next Monday).

Next semester's CS160 is pretty compact with only 90 spots. Based on the data from Berkeley time at the 5th day of phase1 there will be already around 150 people on the waitlist. With that saying, if I'm on the 150th of waitlist for a 90 spots class like CS160, what's the chance of getting into the class at the end? 

Also, if I couldn't make it CS160 for the next semester, are there any substitute classes to take to help me get into the context of HCI research? I'm thinking IEOR170, which can be took as a tech elec. Anyone took it before can share some opinions?
history.subject: CS160 for phase1?
